A DNS zone is usually a single domain (though not always).&lt;br&gt;
A zone file is composed of many DNS resource records (RRs).&lt;br&gt;
There are many different types of RRs.&lt;br&gt;
Let&amp;rsquo;s record some common ones.&lt;/p&gt;
